        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Air raid sirens sound, blasts heard in Jerusalem Middle East Issued on: 07/03/2026 - 11:52 Air raid sirens have sounded in Jerusalem. At least three explosions were heard, and over the past 24 hours at least six air raid alerts have been issued across Israel. FRANCE24 correspondent Noga Tarnopolsky reports the latest from Jerusalem. Humanitarian crisis looming: 300,000 displaced as Israeli army pounds Lebanon 07/03/2026 Middle East Israel strikes eastern Lebanese town: At least 16 killed in raids on Nabi Chit 07/03/2026 Lebanon Millions of workers facing uncertainty as tensions escalate in the Middle East 07/03/2026 Middle East Russia sharing intelligence information to help Tehran, officials say 07/03/2026 Middle East Israel raids deep into Lebanon: Israeli troops engage Hezbollah after helicopter raid 07/03/2026 Middle East Kurdish Iraq draws a line: Erbil warns against attacks on Iran from Kurdish territory 07/03/2026 Middle East Death toll mounts in Middle East war: Over 1,400 killed across Iran, Lebanon and Israel 07/03/2026 Middle East Lebanon under fire from Israel: Clashes erupts as Israeli forces attempt landing operation 07/03/2026 Middle East Israel carries on targeting Hezbollah strongholds, causing heavy displacement 06/03/2026 Middle East"
