        "link": "https://www.france24.com/en/israel-strikes-eastern-lebanese-town-at-least-16-killed-in-raids-on-nabi-chit",
        "orario": "11:47",
        "timestamp": 1772880446,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Israel strikes eastern Lebanese town: At least 16 killed in raids on Nabi Chit Lebanon Issued on: 07/03/2026 - 11:47 The war has also expanded into Lebanon, where fighting between Hezbollah, a military Iran-backed group, and Israel is continuing. At least 26 people were killed in Israeli airstrikes overnight on the eastern Lebanese town of Nabi Chit, a small mountain community in the Bekaa Valley that has strong ties to Hezbollah’s leadership. Over the past week, Israel has issued evacuation warnings before launching heavy strikes on southern Lebanon and the southern suburbs of Beirut. Tens of thousands of civilians have fled the area. Caitlin Brown reports. Humanitarian crisis looming: 300,000 displaced as Israeli army pounds Lebanon 07/03/2026 Middle East Millions of workers facing uncertainty as tensions escalate in the Middle East 07/03/2026 Middle East Russia sharing intelligence information to help Tehran, officials say 07/03/2026 Middle East Israel raids deep into Lebanon: Israeli troops engage Hezbollah after helicopter raid 07/03/2026 Middle East Kurdish Iraq draws a line: Erbil warns against attacks on Iran from Kurdish territory 07/03/2026 Middle East Death toll mounts in Middle East war: Over 1,400 killed across Iran, Lebanon and Israel 07/03/2026 Middle East Lebanon under fire from Israel: Clashes erupts as Israeli forces attempt landing operation 07/03/2026 Middle East Israel carries on targeting Hezbollah strongholds, causing heavy displacement 06/03/2026 Middle East Iran not 'a week away' from having a nuclear bomb as Trump administration claims 06/03/2026 Middle East"
